16 WHEREAS, as additional testament to their dedication to musical excellence, the Jonesboro
17 Majestic Marching Cardinals proudly represented Georgia at the 2022 National Fourth of
18 July Parade in Washington, D.C., and in 2023, the band was honored with the Music for All
19 "Advocacy in Action" Award; and
20 WHEREAS, through dedication, talent, and perseverance, the Jonesboro Majestic Marching
21 Cardinals continue to inspire young musicians, elevate the performing arts, and bring pride
22 to their community.
23 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
24 recognize and commend the Jonesboro Majestic Marching Cardinals for their outstanding
25 contributions to music education, student enrichment, and the State of Georgia as well as
26 extend best wishes for continued success.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
28 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the Jonesboro
29 Majestic Marching Cardinals.
